The paper proposes a method for data approximation using robust principal graphs, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the method involves image processing. Additionally, the method involves graph theory, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
